               <head>Fragment of a Judeo-Persian letter</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85076240 lccn.loc.gov/sh85033035">
                  <summary>Fragment of a Judeo-Persian letter.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="jpr-Hebr" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="1v" />
                     <author />
                     <title xml:lang="en">Fragment of a letter in Judeo-Persian</title>
                     <note>The author of the letter seems to be describing a prediction, mentions
                correspondence between Yazid b. al-Muhallab b. Abu Sufrah and the Ispahbud (prince
                of Tabaristan), and reports about the sale of sheep (see line 23: רסד צון יזיד פרסתד
                ותן מסמא נזדיק סבאבד - "when Yazid sent the person mentioned to
                Ishpahbad...").</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For transliteration and translation see, Margoliouth, M. A. "An early
                  Judaeo-Persian Document" (1903).</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
